  "prompt": "Can you go on both Kickstarter and Indiegogo at the same time? What are some of the companies who have done it, concurrently or sequentially?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible for a project to be launched on both Kickstarter and Indiegogo at the same time, although doing so must be approached with caution to avoid potential complications such as violations of platform rules, confusion among backers, and issues related to funding and fulfillment. Some creators choose to run a campaign on one platform first and then launch on another, often after the first campaign concludes.\n\nHere are a few key points to consider regarding campaigns run on both platforms:\n\n1. **Sequential Campaigns**: Many creators launch on one platform (commonly Kickstarter) and then follow up with a campaign on another platform (like Indiegogo) to reach a wider audience or to continue funding after a successful initial campaign.\n\n2. **Concurrent Campaigns**: While less common, some projects may choose to run simultaneous campaigns on both platforms, but this can become complicated in terms of managing backers and rewards, especially if there are funding overlaps or if the platforms have differing policies.\n\n### Examples of Companies and Projects \n\n1. **Pebble Technology**: Pebble initially launched on Kickstarter and then followed up with an Indiegogo campaign for the same product, capitalizing on the momentum they built during their Kickstarter success.\n\n2. **Exploding Kittens**: This popular card game was first launched on Kickstarter, where it was extremely successful, and later had an Indiegogo campaign for additional funding and to reach more backers.\n\n3. **Fidget Cube**: Initially launched on Kickstarter, Fidget Cube also made its way to Indiegogo after a very successful Kickstarter campaign, offering additional products and variations.\n\n4. **Anker**: Anker has used both platforms at different times although not necessarily concurrently. They were initially popular on Kickstarter before expanding their brand using Indiegogo for certain product lines.\n\n### Important Considerations\n\n- **Platform Policies**: It's essential to review the terms of service for both Kickstarter and Indiegogo to ensure compliance, particularly regarding the nature of the campaign and intellectual property rights.\n\n- **Backer Communication**: Clear and consistent communication with backers is crucial. This helps avoid confusion, especially regarding the availability of rewards on different platforms.\n\n- **Delivery and Fulfillment**: Managing fulfillment logistics becomes more complex with campaigns on two platforms, so creators need to plan meticulously.\n\nRunning campaigns on both platforms can potentially maximize funding and reach, but it requires careful planning and execution to manage the associated challenges effectively.",
